08/10/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- Thirteen Turkish soldiers were killed on Sunday (October 7th) in clashes between security forces and members of the Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) in Sirnak province, near the Iraqi border. 
Local media reports describe it as one of the largest and most violent attacks against the Turkish Army in years. 
Earlier in the day, Turkish troops killed a member of the PKK in Sirnak.
In other news Sunday, at least four people were injured in an explosion in Istanbul. 
The explosive device reportedly was placed in a garbage bin. 
No one has yet claimed responsibility for the attack. 
(Hurriyet, Sabah, Milliyet, Radikal, Zaman, Bloomberg, CNN, Washington Times - 08/10/07; AFP, Anadolu news agency, BBC, Reuters, al Jazeera, Voice of America, AP, DPA, RIA Novosti, CNN Turk - 07/10/07)
